O(n^2)

Iteration start from n when i=0 then n-1, n-2 until hitting the last iteration, which is 0;

So the total iteration will be n + (n-1) + (n - 2) + 。。。+ 0 = O(N^2)

For every ith element the second loop runs n-(i+1) times.
In the first for loop when i=0, the second loop runs n-1 times&lt;br&gt;
Similarly when i=1 second loop runs n-2 times&lt;br&gt;.&lt;br&gt;.&lt;br&gt;.&lt;br&gt;
when i=n-2 second loop runs 1 time.&lt;br&gt;
when i=n-1 second loop runs 0 times.&lt;br&gt;
O(n-1)+O(n-2)+......+O(1)+0 =&gt; O(n)&lt;br&gt;
Hence the total algorithm&#39;s time compexity is O(n*n) = O(n^2)

