You can parametrize your `AbstractListFragment` class with a type of view model:
```
abstract class AbstractListViewModel()

abstract class AbstractListFragment&lt;T : AbstractListViewModel&gt;() {
    abstract var viewModel: T
}

class ChildListViewModel() : AbstractListViewModel()

class ChildListFragment() : AbstractListFragment&lt;ChildListViewModel&gt;() {
    override lateinit var viewModel: ChildListViewModel
}
```

You have two problems in your code

First, *ChildListFragment* needs to extend *AbstractListFragment* to override its field

    class ChildListFragment() : AbstractListFragment() 

Second, you can&#39;t override var with subclass of property type because it breaks [Liskov Substitution principle][1]. If some method expects *AbstractListFragment*, and you pass *ChildListFragment* there, method could assign some other child of *AbstractListViewModel* to *viewModel*, and *ChildListFragment* would break because it requires exactly *ChildListFragment*

    class AnotherChild() : AbstractListFragment()

    fun someMethod(AbstractListFragment fragment) {
        fragment.viewModel = AnotherChild() // &lt;= here ChildListFragment would expect ChildListViewModel but would get AnotherChild
    }

    fun main() {
        someMethod(ChildListFragment())
    }

If you want to return *ChildListViewModel* from *ChildListFragment* you should change *viewModel* to be val

    abstract class AbstractListFragment() {
        abstract val viewModel : AbstractListViewModel
    }

    class ChildListFragment() : AbstractListFragment() {
        override val viewModel : ChildListViewModel
    }

You can use baking lateinit field like the following:

    class ChildListFragment() : AbstractListFragment() {
        private lateinit var _viewModel: ChildListViewModel
    
        override val viewModel : ChildListViewModel by lazy {
            _viewModel
        }
    }

Or you can use some other techniques like MVP (see [Moxy library][2], for example).


  [1]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liskov_substitution_principle
  [2]: https://github.com/Arello-Mobile/Moxy

